# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for sensitive paths.
#
# WHY: The OpenSSF Scorecard "Code-Review" check looks for this file as
# evidence that changes go through review. For a single-maintainer repo
# the file primarily documents ownership, but it also wires up GitHub's
# auto-request-review so a future co-maintainer is automatically tagged
# without having to remember which paths are sensitive.
#
# The catch-all at the end declares the maintainer for any path not
# explicitly listed; the more-specific lines above it govern the
# supply-chain hot paths (workflows, release scripts, security policy,
# package.json files that drive `npm publish`).
#
# REFERENCE: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# CI / CD / supply-chain hot paths — anything here can ship to npm or
# touch repository secrets, so review must not be skipped.
/.github/                       @kensaurus
/.github/workflows/             @kensaurus
/.github/dependabot.yml         @kensaurus
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @kensaurus
/.npmrc                         @kensaurus
/pnpm-workspace.yaml            @kensaurus

# Release tooling — `pnpm release` is the only path that publishes to
# npm. A change here can silently neutralise the publish-readiness,
# tarball-verify, or workspace-protocol guards.
/scripts/check-publish-readiness.mjs        @kensaurus
/scripts/check-workspace-protocol.mjs       @kensaurus
/scripts/verify-published-tarballs.mjs      @kensaurus
/scripts/check-no-secrets.mjs               @kensaurus
/scripts/install-git-hooks.mjs              @kensaurus

# Security policy + license — never edited as part of a normal PR.
/SECURITY.md                    @kensaurus
/LICENSE                        @kensaurus

# Package manifests that drive what gets published. A typo or a missing
# `files`/`exports`/`publishConfig` field breaks every external install.
/packages/*/package.json        @kensaurus
/package.json                   @kensaurus

# Catch-all
*                               @kensaurus
